rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
Primary entity representing the collection of all automobile models. A motor vehicle model is a particular brand of vehicle sold by a manufacturer. In cars, the model is usually defined by a common chassis, but it can also represent a marketing segment. For motorcycles, it is a common frame.
Things That Are An Automobile Model:
## Models of cars (e.g.: Toyota Camry, Hyundai Tiburon, Ford Taurus, Rolls Royce Phantom).
## Models of SUVs and trucks (e.g.: Hummer H3, Jeep Commander, Nissan hardbody truck, Dodge Ram).
## Prototype Models (e.g.: Phantom Corsair).
## Models of mopeds and motorcycles (e.g. Piaggio Ciao, Harley-Davidson Sportster).
Things That Are NOT An Automobile Model:
## Vehicles from different model years (e.g. 2007 Ford Focus Sedan, 2008 Ford Focus Sedan). These should be instances of mso:automotive.model_year.
## Automobile Make (e.g. Aston Martin, Honda). These should be instances of mso:automotive.make.
## Automotive class (e.g. Crossover SUV, Pony car, Concept car). These should be instances of mso:automotive.body_style.
## Trim levels of model years(e.g. 2009 Toyota Camry SE, Toyota Camry XLE). These should be instances of mso:automotive.trim_level.
## Fictional automobiles (e.g. Herbie the Love Bug, Chitty Chitty Bang Bang, Batmobile). Use mso:fictional_universe.object in these cases.
## Personally-owned automobiles (e.g. Elvis' Pink Cadillac). Use mso:automotive.vehicle in thse cases.
## Aircraft models (e.g. Concorde, Skyship 600). These should be instances of mso:aviation.aircraft_model.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Automobile Model

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the class of all engine transmissions.
